    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>A hurlbat is a throwing axe made from a single piece of flat metal. Every extremity of the hurlbat is sharpened, including the point of the handle.</em></p>\n<p>You can wield the hurlbat as a melee weapon, but it&rsquo;s not designed for such use; you take a &ndash;1 penalty on melee&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Attack-Roll\">attack rolls</a>&nbsp;with the weapon, and you must succeed at a DC 15&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Reflex\">Reflex</a>&nbsp;save when making melee attacks to avoid cutting yourself on an edge and taking 1 point of slashing damage. You don&rsquo;t need to attempt this save while wearing heavy armor.</p>",
